 * @page culite_tutorial_datatypes Datatypes
 * @details cuLite uses the following datatypes:
 *
 * @code
 *
 * culite::int_t i; // integer
 * culite::uint_t u; // unsigned integer
 *
 * culite::real_t d; // double precision real (double)
 * culite::real4_t s; // single precision real (float)
 * culite::complex_t z; // double precision complex (cuDoubleComplex)
 * culite::complex8_t c; // single precision complex (cuFloatComplex)
 *
 * @endcode
 *
 * For 32-bit integer length, link with the default library (libculite.so / culite.lib).@n 
 * For 64-bit integer length add -DCULITE_I64 to your compilation flags and link with the i64 library (libculite_i64.so / culite_i64.lib).
 *
 *
